# X11 [truetype fonts]
# Inconsolata:    extremely good Latin monospace terminal font
# DejaVu:         comprehensive Sans/Serif/Mono
# SIL Charis:     comprehensive Roman/Cyrillic optimized for printing
# SIL Gentium:    very readable Latin/Greek
# SIL Arabic:     extended Arabic script, Scheherazade/Lateef
# Farsi:          Persian script, Elham/Homa/Koodak/Nazli/Roya/Terafik/Titr
# CLM Culmus:     Hebrew script, David/Frank Ruehl/Miriam(=Sans/Serif/Mono)/...
# SIL Abyssinica: Ethiopic script
# SIL Padauk:     all standard Myanmar characters [Graphite not supported]
# WenQuanYi:      CJKV glyphs, Hei-Ti (Sans)
# Lohit:          Hindi script, Assamese/Bengali/Gujarati/Hindi/Kannada/Konkani/Kashmiri/Maithili/Malayalam/Marathi/Nepali/Oriya/Punjabi/Sindhi/Tamil/Telugu
# Bangla:         Bengali script, Akaash/Ani/Likhan/Mitra Mono/Mukti Narrow
# ThaiFonts:      Thai script, Garuda/Kinnari/Loma/Norasi/Umpush/Waree/Purisa/Sawasdee/Tlwg
# Khmer OS:       Khmer script (Cambodia), Battambang/Bokor/Content/Fasthand/Freehand/Metal Chrieng/Muol/Siemreap/System
# TibMachUni:     Tibetan, Dzongkha and Ladakhi scripts
# LKLUG:          [Extra] Sinhala (Sri Lanka) script
# Mv:             [Extra] Dhivehi (Maldives) script, Elaaf/MAG Round/Lady Luck/Sehga/Galan/Iyyu/GroupX Avas
# [Cham:          www.ling.hawaii.edu/~uhdoc/champa/chamHI.ttf, incorrect codepoints]
# Essays1743:     Nice decorative Latin font
